####  Stay true to the web

People expect web app pages to load fast. On the server, React lets you start
streaming HTML while you’re still fetching data, progressively filling in the
remaining content before any JavaScript code loads. On the client, React can
use standard web APIs to keep your UI responsive even in the middle of
rendering.

