###  Updating objects and arrays in state

You can put objects and arrays into state. In React, state is considered read-
only, so **you should _replace_ it rather than _mutate_ your existing objects
** . For example, if you have a ` form ` object in state, don’t mutate it:



    // 🚩 Don't mutate an object in state like this:  


    form.firstName = 'Taylor';

Instead, replace the whole object by creating a new one:



    // ✅ Replace state with a new object  


    setForm({  


      ...form,  


      firstName: 'Taylor'  


    });

Read [ updating objects in state ](/learn/updating-objects-in-state) and [
updating arrays in state ](/learn/updating-arrays-in-state) to learn more.

